Strozier Library Learning District

Back to top

In-Person Tutoring at Strozier Library

Sunday - Wednesday
8pm to midnight

We are located on the first floor of Strozier Library across from Starbucks.

Online Tutoring

 

Please note: tutors will only be available during our posted active hours and, for privacy and security reasons, you will be asked to log in with your my.fsu credentials before you can reach the direct Zoom link.

Need help figuring out Zoom?

How to Access Online Tutoring with Zoom will walk you through downloading and signing into Zoom, finding the link to the active tutoring session, and what happens when you log in for the first time.

If you are a TCC or FAMU student and would like to access tutoring for the current semester, please email lib-tutoring@fsu.edu or use the Submit A Question page to register and receive the link.

AXS Chemistry Tutoring at Dirac Science Library

Back to top

Chemistry Tutoring at Dirac

In Dirac, chemistry tutoring is available in person!

Tuesday & Thursday
6pm to 8pm

This service supports both levels of general and organic chemistry, and the AXS tutors will be available on the first floor of Dirac near Starbucks.

This chemistry tutoring service is provided by Alpha Chi Sigma.

Reading and Writing Center

Back to top

Reading and Writing Center

Monday through Thursday
5pm to 8pm
First Floor in the Learning District or Basement, room 005C

Make an Appointment

This location takes appointments and walk-ins, but walk-ins can only be accommodated if there is a consultant available at the time. To ensure you get the help you need, we encourage you to make an appointment.

Please Note:The most up-to-date information on sites, hours, and appointments will be found on the official RWC homepage. Please verify details on this site if you have any questions.
